headline: Domino’s Pizza price target raised to $515 from $500 at BMO Capital
summary: BMO Capital analyst Andrew Strelzik raised the firm’s price target on Domino’s Pizza (DPZ) to $515 from $500 and keeps an Outperform rating on the shares. The company’s Q4 EPS achieved consensus as softer U.S. comps were offset by favorable G&A and supply chain profits and the management reiterated 2025 guidance for global retail sales growth consistent with 2024, the analyst tells investors in a research note.
